## Comprehensive Report on llama.cpp Chat Template System

### Architecture Overview

The chat template system in llama.cpp uses a two-tier approach:
1. **Jinja-based templates** (modern, flexible) - primary system
2. **Legacy C++ handlers** (hardcoded for specific models) - fallback system

---

### Key Files

| File Path | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `/common/chat.h` | Main header with struct definitions and function declarations |
| `/common/chat.cpp` | Core implementation (1963 lines) |
| `/src/llama-chat.h` | Legacy template enum and function declarations |
| `/src/llama-chat.cpp` | Legacy C++ template handlers |
| `/common/chat-auto-parser.h` | Auto-parser analysis framework |
| `/tests/test-chat-template.cpp` | Test suite |

---

### Core Structures

#### 1. Chat Template Container (`common/chat.h`, line 52-79)
```cpp
struct common_chat_template {
    jinja::program prog;           // Parsed Jinja2 template
    std::string bos_tok;           // BOS token
    std::string eos_tok;           // EOS token
    std::string src;               // Template source
    chat_template_caps caps;       // Template capabilities
};
```

#### 2. Chat Templates Manager (`common/chat.cpp`, line 223-229)
```cpp
struct common_chat_templates {
    bool add_bos;
    bool add_eos;
    bool has_explicit_template;
    std::unique_ptr<common_chat_template> template_default;
    std::unique_ptr<common_chat_template> template_tool_use;
};
```

---

### Template Initialization & Auto-Detection

#### Main Entry Point
**File**: `common/chat.cpp`, **Line**: 591-689

```cpp
common_chat_templates_ptr common_chat_templates_init(
    const struct llama_model * model,
    const std::string & chat_template_override,
    const std::string & bos_token_override = "",
    const std::string & eos_token_override = "");
```

**Flow**:
1. If no override provided, extracts template from model metadata via `llama_model_chat_template(model, nullptr)`
2. Also tries to extract tool-specific template variant via `llama_model_chat_template(model, "tool_use")`
3. Falls back to `CHATML_TEMPLATE_SRC` if empty
4. Creates `common_chat_template` objects by parsing Jinja2 with `jinja::lexer` and `jinja::parse_from_tokens()`
5. Returns `common_chat_templates_ptr` (unique_ptr wrapper)

**Key Line 614-620**: Falls back to ChatML template if default is empty or explicitly "chatml"

---

### Template Application Dispatch

**File**: `common/chat.cpp`, **Line**: 1872-1877

```cpp
common_chat_params common_chat_templates_apply(
    const struct common_chat_templates * tmpls,
    const struct common_chat_templates_inputs & inputs) {
    GGML_ASSERT(tmpls != nullptr);
    return inputs.use_jinja ? 
        common_chat_templates_apply_jinja(tmpls, inputs) :
        common_chat_templates_apply_legacy(tmpls, inputs);
}
```

**Two Routes**:
1. **Jinja Route** (line 1693) - Modern, supports reasoning, tools, streaming
2. **Legacy Route** (line 1807) - Direct C++ implementations

---

### Specialized Template Detection

**File**: `common/chat.cpp`, **Line**: 1634-1691

Function: `std::optional<common_chat_params> common_chat_try_specialized_template()`

Detects and routes to specialized handlers based on template string patterns:

#### Ministral/Magistral Large 3 Detection (Lines 1640-1643)
```cpp
if (src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") != std::string::npos && 
    src.find("[TOOL_CALLS]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[ARGS]") != std::string::npos && 
    src.find("[CALL_ID]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Ministral/Magistral Large 3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_ministral_3(tmpl, params);
}
```

**Key insight**: Mistral Small 3.2 uses `[CALL_ID]` which Ministral doesn't - this distinguishes them.

#### Other Specialized Handlers (Lines 1646-1687)
- **GPT-OSS** - detects `<|channel|>`
- **Functionary v3.2** - detects `>>>all` + `>>>${recipient}`
- **Kimi K2 Thinking** - detects `<|tool_calls_section_begin|>` + `<|tool_call_begin|>`
- **LFM2** - detects `<|tool_list_start|>` + `<|tool_list_end|>`
- **LFM2.5** - detects `List of tools: [`
- **GigaChatV3** - detects `<|role_sep|>` + `<|message_sep|>` (without `<|function_call|>`)

---

### Ministral-3 Handler Implementation

**File**: `common/chat.cpp`, **Line**: 825-940

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_ministral_3(
    const common_chat_template & tmpl,
    const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    // Converts messages to Ministral format with thinking blocks
    auto adjusted_messages = json::array();
    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role = msg.value("role", "");
        if (role != "system" && role != "assistant") {
            adjusted_messages.push_back(msg);
            continue;
        }

        auto content = json::array();

        // Add reasoning_content as "thinking" block
        if (msg.contains("reasoning_content") && msg.at("reasoning_content").is_string()) {
            content.push_back({
                {"type", "thinking"},
                {"thinking", msg.at("reasoning_content").get<std::string>()}
            });
        }

        // Add content as "text" block
        if (msg.contains("content")) {
            if (msg.at("content").is_string()) {
                content.push_back({
                    {"type", "text"},
                    {"text", msg.at("content").get<std::string>()}
                });
            } else if (msg.at("content").is_array()) {
                auto blocks = msg.at("content");
                content.insert(content.end(), blocks.begin(), blocks.end());
            }
        }

        auto adjusted = msg;
        adjusted["content"] = content;
        adjusted.erase("reasoning_content");
        adjusted_messages.push_back(adjusted);
    }

    // Apply template with adjusted messages
    data.supports_thinking = true;
    data.thinking_start_tag = "[THINK]";
    data.thinking_end_tag = "[/THINK]";
    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(
        tmpl, inputs, /* messages_override = */ adjusted_messages);
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.preserved_tokens = {
        "[THINK]", "[/THINK]", "[TOOL_CALLS]", "[ARGS]"
    };

    // Builds PEG parser for:
    // - Reasoning blocks: [THINK]...[/THINK]
    // - Tool calls with [TOOL_CALLS][ARGS] markers
    // - JSON schema responses wrapped in ```json ... ```
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        auto generation_prompt = p.prefix(inputs.generation_prompt, "[THINK]");
        auto reasoning = extract_reasoning ? 
            p.optional("[THINK]" + p.reasoning(p.until("[/THINK]")) + "[/THINK]") : 
            p.eps();

        // ... JSON schema, tool calls, or content-only parsing ...
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**Key Points**:
- Converts system and assistant messages to content array format with `{"type": "thinking"}` or `{"type": "text"}` blocks
- Uses `[THINK]`/`[/THINK]` markers for thinking blocks
- Uses `[TOOL_CALLS]` and `[ARGS]` markers for tool calls
- Generates PEG parser for streaming-aware parsing
- Supports parallel tool calls if enabled

---

### Legacy Template System

**File**: `src/llama-chat.h`, **Line**: 7-62

