# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

llama.cpp's `common/chat.cpp` has a two-tier system for chat template handling:
1. **Jinja-based templates** — the primary path, using `common_chat_templates_apply_jinja`
2. **Specialized C++ handlers** — override the auto-parser for specific model families

The function `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (line 1634 in `common/chat.cpp`) checks template source patterns and routes to hardcoded handlers (e.g., `common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`).

The Mistral Instruct v0.3 format (used by Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407 and similar models) has no dedicated handler today — it falls through to the auto-parser. The task is to add one. The format:

- Prepends system message into the first user turn: `[INST]system\n\nuser[/INST]`
- Regular user turns: `[INST]user[/INST]`
- Assistant turns: `content</s>`
- Tool calls: `[TOOL_CALLS][{"name":"…","arguments":{…},"id":"…"}]`
- No `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` markers (unlike Ministral 3 / Devstral)
- Has `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` (unlike Llama 2, which also uses `[INST]`)

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `common/chat.cpp` | **Only file to change** — add handler function + detection block |
| `common/chat-peg-parser.cpp` | Reference only: `standard_json_tools()` is defined here and available via `p.standard_json_tools(...)` in any `build_chat_peg_parser` lambda |
| `common/chat-peg-parser.h` | Reference only: `standard_json_tools` declared at line 108 |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` | Reference only: the exact Jinja template this handler targets |

**Do NOT modify:** `src/llama-chat.h`, `src/llama-chat.cpp`, or any existing handler function.

---

## Implementation

### Step 1 — Add the handler function in `common/chat.cpp`

**Insert after line 940** (after the closing `}` of `common_chat_params_init_ministral_3`, before `common_chat_params_init_gpt_oss`).

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 format (Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407 and similar)
// See: https://huggingface.co/mistralai/Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407
// Format: <s>[INST]system\n\nuser[/INST] assistant</s>[INST]user[/INST]
// Tool calls: [TOOL_CALLS][{"name":"…","arguments":{…},"id":"…"}]</s>
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    data.prompt            = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format            = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    data.supports_thinking = false;
    data.preserved_tokens  = {
        "[TOOL_CALLS]",
        "[/INST]",
    };

    auto has_tools       = inputs.tools.is_array() && !inputs.tools.empty();
    auto include_grammar = has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE;

    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        if (has_tools && inputs.tool_choice != COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_NONE) {
            // Mistral Nemo tool call format:
            //   [TOOL_CALLS][{"name":"fn","arguments":{…},"id":"abcdefghi"}]
            // `array_wrapped = true` wraps the call object(s) in a JSON array.
            // `call_id_key = "id"` captures the mandatory 9-char alphanumeric id.
            auto tool_calls = p.standard_json_tools(
                /* section_start    = */ "[TOOL_CALLS]",
                /* section_end      = */ "",
                /* tools            = */ inputs.tools,
                /* parallel_calls   = */ inputs.parallel_tool_calls,
                /* force_calls      = */ inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_REQUIRED,
                /* name_key         = */ "name",
                /* args_key         = */ "arguments",
                /* array_wrapped    = */ true,
                /* function_is_key  = */ false,
                /* call_id_key      = */ "id",
                /* gen_call_id_key  = */ "",
                /* parameters_order = */ {"name", "arguments", "id"}
            );
            return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) +
                   p.content(p.until("[TOOL_CALLS]")) +
                   tool_calls;
        }

        // Content-only path (no tools or tool_choice == NONE)
        include_grammar = false;
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest());
    });

    data.parser = parser.save();

    if (include_grammar) {
        data.grammar_lazy = inputs.tool_choice == COMMON_CHAT_TOOL_CHOICE_AUTO;
        data.grammar = build_grammar([&](const common_grammar_builder & builder) {
            foreach_function(inputs.tools, [&](const json & tool) {
                const auto & function = tool.at("function");
                auto         schema   = function.at("parameters");
                builder.resolve_refs(schema);
            });
            parser.build_grammar(builder, data.grammar_lazy);
        });
        data.grammar_triggers = {
            { COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD, "[TOOL_CALLS]" }
        };
    }

    return data;
}
```

---

### Step 2 — Add auto-detection in `common_chat_try_specialized_template`

**Insert after line 1644** (after the closing `}` of the Ministral 3 block, before the `// GPT-OSS` comment at line 1646).

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 (Nemo format):
    //   [INST]/[/INST] user turns, system prepended to first user turn, </s> after assistant.
    //   Uses [AVAILABLE_TOOLS] (distinguishes from plain Llama-2 [INST] format).
    //   Absent [SYSTEM_PROMPT] distinguishes this from Ministral/Mistral-Large-3 / Devstral.
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

---

## Detection Logic Rationale

| Template family | `[INST]` | `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` | `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` | Result |
|-----------------|----------|---------------------|-------------------|--------|
| Ministral 3 / Devstral | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | Caught **earlier** by Ministral 3 block (lines 1640-1644) |
| Mistral v7 / v7-tekken | ✓ | ✗ | ✓ | `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent check fails → not matched |
| Llama 2 (all variants) | ✓ | ✗ | ✗ | `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` absent → not matched |
| **Mistral Nemo (v0.3)** | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ | **Matches new block** |

Because the Ministral 3 block runs first, any template with `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]` is already consumed. The new block only fires if `[AVAILABLE_TOOLS]` is present but `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` is not.

---

## Reused Utilities (existing, not modified)

| Utility | Location | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl` | `common/chat.cpp` ~line 820 | Renders Jinja prompt |
| `build_chat_peg_parser` | `common/chat.cpp` | Lambda-based PEG parser builder |
| `p.standard_json_tools(...)` | `common/chat-peg-parser.cpp` line 901 | Builds parser + grammar for JSON-array tool calls |
| `build_grammar` | `common/chat.cpp` | Compiles grammar from PEG parser |
| `foreach_function` | `common/chat.cpp` | Iterates tool definitions |
| `COMMON_GRAMMAR_TRIGGER_TYPE_WORD` | headers | Grammar trigger on `[TOOL_CALLS]` prefix |

---

## Verification

1. **Manual smoke test** — run the test tool against the Mistral Nemo jinja template:
   ```bash
   ./bin/test-chat-template models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja
   ./bin/test-chat-template models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja --with-tools
   ```
   Confirm the log line `"Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3"` appears.

2. **Automated test suite**:
   ```bash
   ./bin/test-chat-template
   ```
   All existing tests must still pass (no existing handler was modified).

3. **Negative check** — verify Ministral 3 / Devstral templates still route to their own handler, not the new one, by checking the debug log output for those templates.

4. **Format correctness** — compare prompt output between the new handler and a direct Jinja render (`--no-common` flag in the test tool) for the Mistral Nemo template; they should be identical since `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl` is used unchanged.

